        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Issuance & Verification"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The two operational flows in Microsoft Entra Verified ID are issuance (giving a credential to a holder) and verification (asking a holder to prove a credential). Both flows use the Request Service API \u2014 a REST API your application calls to initiate the flow \u2014 and receive real-time status via webhook callbacks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Side-by-side sequence diagrams of the Entra Verified ID issuance flow (left) and verification flow (right)",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prerequisites"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
