      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Getting an Access Token for the Request Service API"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Request Service API uses the scope 3db474b9-6a0c-4840-96ac-1fceb342124f/.default. Your application acquires a token with client credentials (daemon) or on-behalf-of (user-delegated) and sends it as a Bearer token on every API call."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import msal, os\n\nTENANT_ID     = os.environ['AZURE_TENANT_ID']\nCLIENT_ID     = os.environ['AZURE_CLIENT_ID']\nCLIENT_SECRET = os.environ['AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET']\n\nVC_SCOPE = '3db474b9-6a0c-4840-96ac-1fceb342124f/.default'\nAUTHORITY = f'https://login.microsoftonline.com/{TENANT_ID}'\n\n# Confidential client \u2014 client credentials flow\napp = msal.ConfidentialClientApplication(\n    client_id=CLIENT_ID,\n    client_credential=CLIENT_SECRET,\n    authority=AUTHORITY,\n)\n\ndef get_vc_token():\n    result = app.acquire_token_for_client(scopes=[VC_SCOPE])\n    if 'access_token' not in result:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Token error: {result.get('error_description')}\")\n    return result['access_token']"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Full Issuance Flow Implementation (Flask)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The issuance flow consists of two endpoints: one that creates the issuance request and returns the QR code URL to the frontend, and one callback that receives status from the Entra Verified ID service when the credential is issued."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Create Issuance Request"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import requests, uuid, os\nfrom flask import Flask, request, jsonify, session\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\napp.secret_key = os.environ['FLASK_SECRET']\n\nTENANT_ID      = os.environ['AZURE_TENANT_ID']\nISSUER_DID     = os.environ['ISSUER_DID']           # did:web:verifiedid.contoso.com\nMANIFEST_URL   = os.environ['VC_MANIFEST_URL']\nCALLBACK_KEY   = os.environ['VC_CALLBACK_API_KEY']\nCALLBACK_HOST  = os.environ['APP_PUBLIC_URL']        # https://app.contoso.com\nVC_ENDPOINT    = f'https://verifiedid.did.msidentity.com/v1.0/{TENANT_ID}/verifiableCredentials'\n\n@app.route('/api/issuance/start', methods=['POST'])\ndef start_issuance():\n    state = str(uuid.uuid4())          # ties callback to this browser session\n    session['vc_state'] = state\n\n    # Get employee claims from your HR system or Entra ID\n    claims = {\n        'displayName': session.get('user_name', 'Unknown'),\n        'jobTitle':    session.get('user_title', ''),\n        'department':  session.get('user_dept', ''),\n    }\n\n    payload = {\n        'includeQRCode': True,\n        'callback': {\n            'url':     f'{CALLBACK_HOST}/api/issuance/callback',\n            'state':   state,\n            'headers': {'api-key': CALLBACK_KEY},\n        },\n        'authority':    ISSUER_DID,\n        'registration': {'clientName': 'Contoso Employee Portal'},\n        'type':         'VerifiedEmployee',\n        'manifest':     MANIFEST_URL,\n        'claims':       claims,\n    }\n\n    resp = requests.post(\n        f'{VC_ENDPOINT}/createIssuanceRequest',\n        headers={'Authorization': f'Bearer {get_vc_token()}', 'Content-Type': 'application/json'},\n        json=payload,\n        timeout=10,\n    )\n    resp.raise_for_status()\n    data = resp.json()\n\n    return jsonify({\n        'requestId': data['requestId'],\n        'qrCode':    data.get('qrCode'),\n        'url':       data.get('url'),\n    })"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Issuance Callback Handler"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# In-memory status store \u2014 use Redis or a DB in production\nissuance_status = {}\n\n@app.route('/api/issuance/callback', methods=['POST'])\ndef issuance_callback():\n    if request.headers.get('api-key') != CALLBACK_KEY:\n        return '', 401\n\n    data    = request.get_json(force=True)\n    state   = data.get('state')\n    status  = data.get('requestStatus')\n\n    # Store status keyed by state so the frontend can poll\n    issuance_status[state] = {\n        'status':  status,\n        'subject': data.get('subject'),\n    }\n    return '', 200\n\n@app.route('/api/issuance/status', methods=['GET'])\ndef issuance_status_poll():\n    state = session.get('vc_state')\n    entry = issuance_status.get(state, {'status': 'pending'})\n    return jsonify(entry)\n\n# Frontend polls /api/issuance/status every 2s until status == 'issuance_successful'"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Full Verification Flow Implementation (Flask)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Create Presentation Request"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "@app.route('/api/verification/start', methods=['POST'])\ndef start_verification():\n    state = str(uuid.uuid4())\n    session['verify_state'] = state\n\n    payload = {\n        'includeQRCode': True,\n        'callback': {\n            'url':     f'{CALLBACK_HOST}/api/verification/callback',\n            'state':   state,\n            'headers': {'api-key': CALLBACK_KEY},\n        },\n        'authority':    ISSUER_DID,\n        'registration': {'clientName': 'Contoso Partner Access'},\n        'requestedCredentials': [\n            {\n                'type':    'VerifiedEmployee',\n                'purpose': 'Verify your employment status to access partner resources.',\n                'acceptedIssuers': [ISSUER_DID],\n                'configuration': {\n                    'validation': {\n                        'allowRevoked':         False,\n                        'validateLinkedDomain': True,\n                    }\n                },\n            }\n        ],\n    }\n\n    resp = requests.post(\n        f'{VC_ENDPOINT}/createPresentationRequest',\n        headers={'Authorization': f'Bearer {get_vc_token()}', 'Content-Type': 'application/json'},\n        json=payload,\n        timeout=10,\n    )\n    resp.raise_for_status()\n    data = resp.json()\n\n    return jsonify({'requestId': data['requestId'], 'qrCode': data.get('qrCode'), 'url': data.get('url')})"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Presentation Callback Handler"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "verification_results = {}\n\n@app.route('/api/verification/callback', methods=['POST'])\ndef verification_callback():\n    if request.headers.get('api-key') != CALLBACK_KEY:\n        return '', 401\n\n    data   = request.get_json(force=True)\n    state  = data.get('state')\n    status = data.get('requestStatus')\n\n    if status == 'presentation_verified':\n        creds = data.get('verifiedCredentialsData', [])\n        claims = {}\n        for cred in creds:\n            if 'VerifiedEmployee' in cred.get('type', []):\n                rev = cred.get('credentialState', {}).get('revocationStatus')\n                if rev != 'VALID':\n                    verification_results[state] = {'status': 'failed', 'reason': 'revoked'}\n                    return '', 200\n                claims = cred.get('claims', {})\n\n        verification_results[state] = {'status': 'verified', 'claims': claims}\n    else:\n        verification_results[state] = {'status': status}\n\n    return '', 200\n\n@app.route('/api/verification/status', methods=['GET'])\ndef verification_status_poll():\n    state = session.get('verify_state')\n    result = verification_results.get(state, {'status': 'pending'})\n    # Strip claims from the polling response \u2014 only return what the UI needs\n    if result.get('status') == 'verified':\n        return jsonify({'status': 'verified', 'displayName': result['claims'].get('displayName', '')})\n    return jsonify({'status': result.get('status', 'pending')})"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Face Check (Liveness Verification)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Microsoft Entra Verified ID supports Face Check \u2014 a liveness detection step that matches the user's selfie against the photo claim in their VC. This adds a strong anti-spoofing layer for high-value verification scenarios (KYC, high-privilege access) without storing biometric data on your servers."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Face Check requires an Azure AI Face resource in the same subscription. The photo claim must be present and indexed in the VC. The liveness check runs on the device \u2014 the photo is never sent to your server."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Presentation request with Face Check enabled\n# Requires: photo claim in VC, Azure Face resource, 'faceCheck' extension\npayload = {\n    'includeQRCode': True,\n    'callback': { ... },\n    'authority': ISSUER_DID,\n    'registration': {'clientName': 'High-Assurance Access Portal'},\n    'requestedCredentials': [\n        {\n            'type':    'VerifiedEmployee',\n            'purpose': 'High-assurance identity verification with liveness check.',\n            'acceptedIssuers': [ISSUER_DID],\n            'configuration': {\n                'validation': {\n                    'allowRevoked':         False,\n                    'validateLinkedDomain': True,\n                }\n            },\n            'extensions': {\n                'faceCheck': {\n                    # 'photo' must be an indexed claim in the VC\n                    'sourcePhotoClaimName': 'photo',\n                    # Confidence threshold: 0.70 = default; increase for higher assurance\n                    'matchConfidenceThreshold': 0.70,\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    ]\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
